  "body": "### Environment information\r\n\r\n* `brownie` Version: `1.18.2`\r\n* `ganache-cli` Version: `6.12.2`\r\n* `solc` Version: `0.8.13`\r\n* Python Version: `3.9.12`\r\n* OS: `macos`\r\n\r\n### What was wrong?\r\n\r\non a sequencer chain like arbitrum one, the `block.number` in solidity returns a number close to the L1 (mainnet) block number ([ref](https://developer.offchainlabs.com/docs/time_in_arbitrum#ethereum-block-numbers-within-arbitrum)). however, it appears when running `block.number` onfork, it actually returns the L2 block number.\r\n\r\nconsider `BlockLogger.sol`:\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\ncontract BlockLogger {\r\n    uint256 public lastBlockSeen;\r\n\r\n    function setLastBlockSeen() public {\r\n        lastBlockSeen = block.number;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nand:\r\n```\r\n>>> contract = BlockLogger.deploy({'from': accounts[0]})\r\nTransaction sent: 0x0a0856ea818758b237b9e58c64220ca0ff0d5c0e6e77ffe20af66ffeaa3c8de5\r\n  Gas price: 0.0 gwei   Gas limit: 12000000   Nonce: 0\r\n  BlockLogger.constructor confirmed   Block: 12484287   Gas used: 84725 (0.71%)\r\n  BlockLogger deployed at: 0x3194cBDC3dbcd3E11a07892e7bA5c3394048Cc87\r\n\r\n>>> contract.lastBlockSeen()\r\n0\r\n>>> contract.setLastBlockSeen()\r\nTransaction sent: 0x6056eee6193e4911271bfc3c00ac7ab09e38e2be38bc1881dc868d1720afe651\r\n  Gas price: 0.0 gwei   Gas limit: 12000000   Nonce: 1\r\n  BlockLogger.setLastBlockSeen confirmed   Block: 12484288   Gas used: 41201 (0.34%)\r\n\r\n<Transaction '0x6056eee6193e4911271bfc3c00ac7ab09e38e2be38bc1881dc868d1720afe651'>\r\n>>> contract.lastBlockSeen()\r\n12484288\r\n```\r\nwhereas current mainnet block height is `14805275`.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nis this a brownie or ganache issue?",
